{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783304099,"nonce":"KXx1BNezOzP4HN/B58aZyCjf3L8=","title":"EPIC: reverse SQL parser + full round-trip fidelity (introspect any dialect INTO the neutral model).","message":"squealy is currently a one-way compiler (Rust/KDL -\u003e model -\u003e dialect SQL). Introspection is\ncolumn-level only: view SELECT bodies come back EMPTY in all backends, check/generated/index\nexpressions are opaque verbatim strings that never normalize (perpetual Alter churn), and whole\nobject classes (triggers, sequences, functions, types/enums/domains, matviews, ...) have no model.\nThe intended design is full round-trip: introspect a live DB of ANY dialect INTO the neutral model,\nthen render OUT to any dialect (\"extract from Postgres, deploy to SQL Server\"). The missing half is\na reverse parser (dialect SQL -\u003e neutral IR).\n\nBackground: 4-backend introspection audit + reverse-parser spike (in ~/.claude/plans/:\nsquealy-introspection-audit.md, squealy-reverse-parser-spike.md, squealy-roundtrip-plan.md).\nThis bug is the ANCHOR for that plan; sub-work is filed/linked as it starts.\n\n- Adopt sqlparser-rs (pinned) as the parse front-end for all dialects. Parser is the cheap ~20-30%;\n  the real work is AST-\u003eExprNode lowering + cross-dialect (semantics-preserving) normalization.\n- WIDEN the neutral IR structurally (general function node, derived tables, view-body set-ops, CTEs,\n  unqualified-column resolution) rather than leaning on opaque Raw fallbacks.\n- Sequence H1 (a squealy-PUBLISHED schema round-trips cleanly) before H2 (arbitrary external DBs + new\n  target dialects like SQL Server).\n- Governing invariant / test spine: render(parse(render(m))) == render(m) -- a published object\n  re-plans to EMPTY.\n\n- [ ] Phase 0 - Foundation: pin sqlparser; Reader seam + normalize module; round-trip identity harness;\n      begin IR widening for H1 constructs.\n- [ ] Phase 1 - Expression normalization (CHECK / generated / index exprs) -\u003e kills Alter churn.\n      (low-risk early win; no view type inference; relates to 108fdfc)\n- [ ] Phase 2 - View-body reconstruction (CREATE VIEW -\u003e ViewQueryModel + view-output type inference)\n      -\u003e SUBSUMES 6a3940a churn half + the deferred churn-free view replan.\n- [ ] Phase 3 - Model unmodeled objects (triggers, sequences, enums/domains, matviews, exclusion\n      constraints, ...) -\u003e SUBSUMES the 6a3940a trigger family (retires PR #81's executor hack).\n- [ ] Phase 4 - External-DB fidelity + widen IR further + add SQL Server target (H2 / the vision).\n\nBucket-A bugs from the audit (independent, small): MySQL ENUM/SET label corruption, MySQL\nexpression-index introspection crash, MySQL prefix-length drop, MySQL ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP\ndrop, PG narrow/wide int round-trip. Also relates to 108fdfc. PR #81 (SQLite trigger capture/replay)\nwas closed as a band-aid superseded by Phase 3.","files":null}]}